{"key":"post-11853332","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11853332</id>\n<content>You mist ALL species from initiation through a few hours before harvest.&amp;nbsp; Old advice not to mist after pins form was back in the early days when people were still using sealed up fruiting chambers.&amp;nbsp; Wet pins would tend to rot or abort with no fresh air.&amp;nbsp; Now that most people are using mini-greenhouses or shotgun terrariums for better performance, mist a few times daily to prevent the substrate from drying out.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If a substrate in a tray is drying out, you can pour water directly around the edges of the tray, floating the substrate.&amp;nbsp; Then, pour out any excess that didn't soak in, a few hours later.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11853451</next>\n<prev>11853324</prev>\n<first>11852890</first>\n<last>11853451</last>\n<when>1263848392</when>\n<utime>01/18/10 10:59 PM</utime>\n</post>"}